The paper describes a recognition system for historical handwritten documents using multi-dimensional recurrent neural networks and connectionist temporal classification. This involves computer vision (cs.CV) for image processing, natural language processing (cs.CL) for recognizing text, machine learning (cs.LG) for training the neural networks, information retrieval (cs.IR) for searching and retrieving relevant documents, and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for the overall intelligent text recognition system.
